Ships a real end-to-end integration test that exercises the full
webhook → signal_stream → SSE pipeline over actual HTTP, and wires
two CI hard-gates around it.

What's new
----------

1. `artifacts/api-server/src/__tests__/e2e/webhook_to_sse_e2e.test.ts`
   — Mounts the REAL `signalHub` singleton (no vi.mock) plus the real
   `streamingRouter`, binds them to a 127.0.0.1 port, and runs four
   tests over raw `http.request` SSE clients:
     • direct publishAlert reaches a subscribed SSE client
     • webhook POST that calls publishAlert reaches the SSE subscriber
     • client filter excludes non-alert events (signal is filtered out)
     • signalHub.status().clientCount reflects live connections
   A unique correlation `tag` is embedded in each payload so events
   from other tests running in parallel on the same singleton don't
   produce false positives. The SSE client is dep-free — raw http +
   a minimal frame parser — matching how the production dashboard
   parses the stream.

2. `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — two changes:
     • updated comment on the api-server regression gate to reflect
       the new test count (3654 → 3658)
     • new hard gate step "Verify e2e test file is present (Phase 14)"
       that `test -f`s the new file path. The e2e test is a
       load-bearing production gate — it's the only test path that
       exercises the hub over real HTTP — so a silent deletion must
       trip a red build.

3. `docs/LAUNCH_CHECKLIST.md`:
     • §2 adds a Phase 14 paragraph describing the new e2e test and
       its CI file-presence gate.
     • production-readiness gate table adds row 13 for Phase 14.
     • updated reference counts to `v1.7.0` (3658 api-server tests).

